author: Ashleigh Davis For Daily Mail Australia
title: Cases of Ross River virus surge on Australia's east coast | Daily Mail Online
text: Spike in mosquito numbers to blame for surge in Ross River virus on east coast of Australia Cases of Ross River virus have surged dramatically on the east coast of Australia There are usually about 5,000 cases reported annually in Australia This year alone there have been 708 cases in Victoria and 436 cases in NSW In the first six weeks of this year 430 people were affected with illness alone Opposition health spokesman Walt Secord has called on the government to spray affected areas and to increase education on the illness Published: 06:29 GMT, 17 February 2017 | Updated: 08:02 GMT, 17 February 2017 171 shares
